三、教學目標 Objectives


Schedule (English seniors) Tuesday: 8:10 to 10:00For this semester, we will continue the practice of speaking, listening and giving presentations. The class is structured with reading, lecture, discussion and group exercise.　


四、課程內容 Course Description


●整體敘述 Overall DescriptionClass Policies Attendance: Attendance will be taken every class. You are expected to attend every class. If you are absent, you are still responsible for assignment and homework and you should check with fellow students NOT the instructor for what you are supposed to do. Any student who is absent more than three times will not be eligible for final exam (which is 40% of your final grade).  A consistent pattern of lateness will also negatively affect your final grade.Preparation and discussion: Read and print out the assigned readings before you attend the class. Raise and answer questions on the topics for discussion. Help each other out when you are involved in a group project. A consistent pattern of enthusiasm will help you earn extra credits and a lack of participation will be evaluated negatively on both the assignments and your final grades.No late assignment. No make-up exam.No cell phone use or Internet surfing in class. You will be asked to leave the class, if you are found engaging in this.


